<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-275-124  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 275 124.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  April 17 1989 v3 n16 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Air Force gives design contracts. (Air Force Logistics Command)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brewin, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Air Force Logistics Command awards design engineering review(DER) contracts worth $625 million.andP;  The contracts will allow theAir Force to place orders for communications and avionicsimprovements without having to prepare requests for proposals(RFPs) for each new job.andP;  Contracts are awarded to: BattelleMemorial Institute, Draper C.S.andP;  Laboratory, Science ApplicationsInternational Corp, Southwest Research Institute and TRW Inc.andO;Under the program, the Air Force will retain rights to productsand improvements.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Defense ContractsUnited States. Air Force. Logistics CommandResearch and DevelopmentPurchasing SystemsAerospace IndustryCommunications TechnologyRequest for Proposals.andO;Person:    Sassler, Stephen (attitudes).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>